definitions: Placing a crown on the head of (someone) as a sign of royalty or honor.
Being the culmination or most significant part of something.
Fitting a dental crown onto a tooth.
Reaching the stage in childbirth where the baby's head becomes visible at the vaginal opening.
examples: The queen was crowning her successor.
The victory was crowning a successful season.
The dentist was crowning the patient's molar.
The midwife announced the baby was crowning.
